feed.title: New Haven Geigerbot
feed.description:
Readings from a DRGB-90 connected directly to a Geigerbot/iPhone 3G via custom cable hack.  I'm using the SB-20/U -Co60 (22) setting for the DRGB-90 as it  uses an SBM-20 tube. 

Readings are in nano-sieverts/hour. To convert to microsieverts (uSv), divide by 1000. So 70 nSv/hr  = 0.07 uSv/hr. 

Feeds 1 & 2 (nSv/h and raw CPM/h) are indoors / fixed in my apartment in Waseda (Shinjuku), Tokyo. Starting in March, the readings will be from my home in New Haven, CT.

Start to Feb 29: Waseda, Shinjuku, Tokyo, Japan
March 1 to now:  New Haven, CT, USA


-----

This is just a test feed, so please don't consider it accurate in any sense except for over time.

Note that I started using a CPM offset of -9 from February 6, 2012 based on my conversations with Nick Dolezal, author of Geigerbot, and my own calculations since then.

Raw CPM from before January 11, 2011 = +/- 0 CPM
Raw CPM from between January 11 - February 6 = CPM + 13
Raw CPM from after February 6 = Raw CPM  (correction factor after Feb 6 = -9)

I wrote up a quick description of my DRGB-90 hack here: http://www.gpsy.com/ev/2012/01/modding-a-drgb90.html
